as published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":37,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":48,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":64,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":66,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":99,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs John Shepey was born in Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England. She married John Shepey before 1540, in Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1515–1545":"1515–1545","1540–1567":"1540–1567","–Female":"Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1567":"1567","1545":"1545","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","before 1540":"enne 1540","1540":"1540","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Bengeworth, Evesham, Worcestershire, England":"Bengeworth, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England":"Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1515–1545":"1515–1545","1540–1567":"1540–1567","–Female":"Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1567":"1567","1545":"1545","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","before 1540":"ennen vuotta 1540","1540":"1540","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Bengeworth, Evesham, Worcestershire, England":"Bengeworth, Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England":"Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1515–1545":"1515–1545","1540–1567":"1540–1567","–Female":"Décédée","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1567":"1567","1545":"1545","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","before 1540":"avant 1540","1540":"1540","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Bengeworth, Evesham, Worcestershire, England":"Bengeworth, Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England":"Bengeworth, Worces